<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Soccer: France Is Upset by Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	World Cup champion France lost to Russia 3-2 Saturday in a  
qualifier for next year's European Championship when Valery Karpin 
scored the go-ahead goal in the 87th minute. 
</P>
<P>
	England's chances of advancing to the 16-team tournament were  
damaged with a scoreless tie at home against Sweden. 
</P>
<P>
	Italy, meanwhile, routed Wales 4-0 at Bologna on goals by  
Christian Vieri, Filippo Inzaghi, Paolo Maldini and Enrico Chiesa. 
</P>
<P>
	At Saint-Denis, Alexander Panov scored twice for Russia, while  
Emmanuel Petit and Sylvain Wiltord scored for France. Ukraine 
(4-0-2) leads Group Four with 14 points while France (3-1-2) in 
third with 11 and Russia (3-3) is fourth with nine. 
</P>
<P>
	The nine group winners qualify along with the top second-place  
team and co-hosts Belgium and the Netherlands. The other eight 
second-place teams go to a playoff for the final four berths. 
</P>
<P>
	After the tie at Wembley, England (2-1-2) is third in Group Five  
with eight points, five behind Sweden (4-0-1) and one behind Poland 
(3-2). England hasn't defeated Sweden since 1968. 
</P>
<P>
	``I suppose we look at a playoff now, which was always a  
possibility,'' England coach Kevin Keegan said. ``We took a bit of 
a knock now, we're down but not out.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Italy (4-0-1) leads Group One with 13 points, while Wales (2-3)  
is third with six points, one behind Switzerland (2-1-1). 
</P>
<P>
	``The next game with Switzerland will be more difficult, because  
the Swiss are traditionally difficult to beat for us, on their home 
field,'' Italy coach Dino Zoff said, looking ahead to Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In other games, Denmark beat Belarus 1-0 in Group One; Norway  
beat Albania, Greece beat Georgia and Slovenia beat Latvia, all by 
2-1 scores in Group Two; Turkey beat Finland 4-2 in Group Three; 
Iceland beat Armenia 2-0 and Ukraine beat Andorra 4-0 in Group 
Four; Spain routed San Marino 9-0 in Group Six; Azerbaijan routed 
Liechtenstein 4-0, Portugal beat Slovakia 1-0 and Romania beat 
Hungary 2-0 in Group Seven; Macedonia and Croatia tied 1-1 in group 
Eight; and Bosnia-Herzegovina beat Lithuania 2-0, the Czech 
Republic beat Estonia 2-0, and Scotland and the Faeroe Islands 
played a 1-1 tie in Group Nine. 
</P>
<P>
	In an exhibition game at Salvador, Brazil and the visiting  
Netherlands played a 2-2 tie in their first meeting since the 
Brazilians won last summer's World Cup semifinal on penalty kicks. 
</P>
<P>
	Amoroso and Giovanni scored first-half goals for Brazil, and  
Patrick Kluivert and Peter van Vossen scored second-half goals for 
the Netherlands. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
