<HEADLINE> Blues Make Bid To Keep Turgeon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- The uncertainty over St. Louis Blues center  
Pierre Turgeon's future appears to be over. 
</P>
<P>
	The team has informed Turgeon that the Blues would give the  
restricted free agent a qualifying offer to retain his rights. 
</P>
<P>
	Turgeon, 29, would have been an unrestricted free agent July 1  
if the Blues had not tendered the qualifying offer. That gives them 
the right to match any offer in the unlikely event he got one as a 
restricted free agent. 
</P>
<P>
	Turgeon led the Blues in playoff scoring with four goals and 13  
points and has scored at least 20 goals in 11 consecutive seasons. 
  	   	
</P>
