<HEADLINE> Quotes From the Belmont Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Quotes from the losing connections after  
Saturday's $1 million Belmont Stakes, in order of finish beginning 
with runner-up Vision and Verse: 
</P>
<P>
	Vision and Verse: ``I'm real pleased with his effort. He was  
doing super coming into the race. He was dead game in the stretch 
and I thought we were going to get there.'' -- trainer Bill Mott. 
</P>
<P>
	Charismatic: ``Heading for the finish, he suddenly dipped  
underneath me and I could tell he was in pain. He gave everything 
he had and ran as hard as he could but he couldn't give the people 
what they wanted.'' -- jockey Chris Antley. 
</P>
<P>
	Best of Luck: ``He didn't run out of track. He was trying hard  
at the finish, he just came up empty.'' -- trainer Allen Jerkens. 
</P>
<P>
	Stephen Got Even: ``We gave it a shot and it didn't work out.  
Stephen was up close to the pace and I thought that they were 
moving pretty quick. A little too quick. He was hung up wide and he 
just flattened out.'' -- trainer Nick Zito. 
</P>
<P>
	Patience Game: ``We got close. I had to be riding him hard the  
whole way. I thought he was giving it everything he had.'' -- jockey 
Kent Desormeaux. 
</P>
<P>
	Silverbulletday: ``I just thank God my filly came back good.  
Bailey, once he turned for home, he just wrapped up on her. He knew 
that was it.'' -- trainer Bob Baffert. 
</P>
<P>
	Menifee: ``It's been a long road. He never gave any indication  
that anything was wrong. It seemed he was tired. We had a tired 
horse today.'' -- trainer Elliott Walden. 
</P>
<P>
	Pineaff: No comments available.  
</P>
<P>
	Prime Directive: No comments available.  
</P>
<P>
	Teletable: ``He just went around the track, that's all.'' --  
jockey John Velazquez. 
</P>
<P>
	Adonis: ``We were in the back of the back and he just didn't  
fire. I jusy eased up on him. '' -- jockey Jorge Chavez. 
  	   	
</P>
