<DOCNO> APW19990605.0028 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-05 20:40:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Son of Maryland Governor Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLLEGE PARK, Md. (AP) -- The teen-age son of Gov. Parris N.  
Glendening was arrested early Saturday on charges of drunken 
driving. 
</P>
<P>
	Raymond H. Glendening pulled into a parking lot at about 2:30  
a.m., shortly after officers responded to a burglar alarm at a 
store. Glendening, 19, told police he stopped because his Chevy 
Blazer had been damaged after he hit a utility pole, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	He failed three sobriety tests and refused to take a  
Breathalyzer test, said police Lt. Andrew Ellis. He was charged 
with driving while intoxicated and driving under the influence of 
alcohol and released on his own recognizance. 
</P>
<P>
	The governor and his wife, Frances, released a statement five  
hours after the arrest of their only child, who recently finished 
his sophomore year of college. 
</P>
<P>
	``Early this morning, we received a call that every parent  
dreads,'' the Glendenings said. ``Today our first duty must be as 
parents. We will offer Raymond our unconditional and abiding love, 
support and guidance.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Glendenings said they would have no further comment until  
the legal proceedings against their son were resolved. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
