<HEADLINE> Hingis Gets Support From Kournikova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- When Martina Hingis left the court after her loss  
to Steffi Graf in the French Open women's final, doubles partner 
Anna Kournikova was there to console her. 
</P>
<P>
	``Anna came to the locker room and hugged me and said, `You were  
better out there,''' Hingis said. 
</P>
<P>
	France's Nathalie Tauziat also helped Hingis cope a little bit  
with her loss. 
</P>
<P>
	Hingis said she didn't really want to come back out to the court  
to accept the runner-up trophy because the crowd was booing her. 
Her mother, Melanie Molitor, convinced her to go back out. 
</P>
<P>
	``If my mother wouldn't have been there, I wouldn't have come  
back,'' Hingis said. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *ANKE, ANDREI AND ANDRE:* Love-struck Andrei Medvedev has made  
it no secret that happiness in his personal life has attributed to 
his success in tennis. But the player he'll meet in Sunday's men's 
final said that being in or out of love doesn't affect his play. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't feel like him that being in love makes any difference  
to me,'' said Andre Agassi, who was recently divorced from actress 
Brooke Shields. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's a good guy and I'm happy to hear that,'' Agassi said of  
Medvedev's romance. ``I prefer if he let his girlfriend play for 
him instead, with all due respect for her game.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Medvedev's girlfriend is Anke Huber, ranked 30th in the world.  
In an interview with French daily Le Parisien on Saturday, Huber 
said she wouldn't want to play for him but she does imagine herself 
in Medvedev's place when she watches him play. 
</P>
<P>
	``I look at his stroke, I try to see what I could do if I was on  
the court, the way I would play,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *NOVOTNA INJURY:* Jana Novotna is still cautious with her  
sprained right ankle. The Wimbledon champion was seen Friday in a 
wheelchair on the Roland Garros grounds to keep the pressure off 
the injured joint. 
</P>
<P>
	Novotna severely sprained her ankle while playing doubles  
Wednesday. The X-rays confirmed that nothing was broken, but there 
is ligament damage. 
</P>
<P>
	It's still unsure whether Novotna will be able to defend her  
title at Wimbledon. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *WILLIAMS &AMP; WILLIAMS:* The Williams sisters advanced to the  
doubles final Saturday when they beat Lindsay Davenport and Mary 
Pierce. 
</P>
<P>
	Venus and Serena Williams will get a shot at a French Open  
doubles title Sunday when they face Martina Hingis and Anna 
Kournikova. 
</P>
<P>
	The men's doubles final was halted Saturday by rain. Mahesh  
Bhupathi and Leander Paes of India led Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia 
and Jeff Tarango of the United States, 6-2, 5-5. The match will be 
continued Sunday. 
  	   	
</P>
