	Buffalo coach Lindy Ruff and assistant Mike Ramsey also were  
part of a Stanley Cup sweep. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's going to be a little easier the second time around,''  
said Ruff, an assistant with Florida in 1996. ``You know you've got 
to keep your players focused and that there's a lot of media 
attention and a lot of things going on.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ramsey played for the Red Wings when they were swept by the New  
Jersey Devils in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	Having failed to grab it once, Zhitnik knows what it takes to  
capture the Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	``Kill to win,'' he said. ``Do anything possible -- score, block  
