<HEADLINE> Giuliani Plans Visit to Arkansas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Mayor Rudolph Giuliani plans an unlikely pit  
stop next month to raise funds for his U.S. Senate campaign: 
Arkansas, the home turf of his possible opponent, First Lady 
Hillary Clinton. 
</P>
<P>
	The mayor's foray into Little Rock, Ark., will turn the tables  
on Mrs. Clinton, who has made 10 visits to New York this year amid 
endless rumors of her candidacy for the seat being vacated next 
year by U.S. Sen. Daniel Moynihan. 
</P>
<P>
	Arkansas Republicans predict the visit could be lucrative for  
Giuliani, who has set up an exploratory committee as he considers a 
Senate race. ``There are some people here who would give money to 
anyone who ran against Hillary Clinton,'' said Chris Carnahan, 
director of the Arkansas GOP. 
</P>
<P>
	An exact date for Giuliani's visit was not set. Giuliani, a  
native New Yorker, has raised Mrs. Clinton's status as an 
out-of-towner on his campaign's Web site, ``HillaryNo.com.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Clinton announced this week that she was opening an  
exploratory committee in July. While Mrs. Clinton has not said 
whether she will seek election, an assortment of Democratic 
officials have said she will run next year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
