<HEADLINE> Examples of Social Promotion Plans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Examples of state policies on social promotion, the practice of  
advancing unprepared students to the next grade so they can stay 
with their age group: 
</P>
<P>
	Promotion based on student test scores: Colorado, Connecticut,  
Delaware, District of Columbia, Florida, Georgia, Illinois, 
Louisiana, South Carolina, Virginia, Wisconsin. 
</P>
<P>
	Promotion based on state and local rules: Maryland  
</P>
<P>
	Promotion based on students' classroom performance: Arkansas,  
Pennsylvania, Texas 
</P>
<P>
	Promotion based on school board-superintendent decision:  
Kentucky, Massachusetts, Minnesota, New Jersey, New York, 
Tennessee, Utah and West Virginia 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	Source: Education Commission of the States  
  	   	
</P>
