<HEADLINE> 'Binks' Actor Thrilled by Part </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Ahmed Best, the man behind the mask of the new  
``Star Wars'' character Jar Jar Binks, feels like he came to the 
scene-stealing role from a galaxy far, far away. 
</P>
<P>
	Before ``Star Wars, Episode I -- The Phantom Menace,'' Best's  
only film experience was working as an extra in ``Lean On Me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``I kept waiting every day for somebody to say, `Excuse me,  
you're not supposed to be here,''' Best says in the June 24 issue 
of Rolling Stone. 
</P>
<P>
	Director George Lucas discovered Best while the  
singer-dancer-drummer was working in the San Francisco production 
of the dance musical ``Stomp.'' Lucas couldn't have been happier 
with his choice. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was the first time I could get an alien to turn in a really  
great performance,'' Lucas said of Best, who acted out the scenes 
during filming in costume, but whose image was digitally created 
and inserted during special effects work later. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
