<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Profiles of American Crash Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	A look at those killed in the crash of American Airlines Flight  
1420 in Little Rock, Ark.: 

</P>
<P>
	--Capt. Richard Buschmann, 48, Naperville, Ill. U.S. Air Force  
Academy graduate, marathon runner, sailor. Fixture at his 
children's soccer and baseball games. A chief pilot for American 
since January, supervising other pilots. Will be buried at Air 
Force Academy. 
</P>
<P>
	--Mary Couch, 68, Havana, Ark. Retired elementary school teacher  
who lived in the house she grew up in. Liked to surf the Internet 
and tell jokes. Had nine cats. 
</P>
<P>
	--Sara Renee ``Sue'' Gray, 78, Russellville, Ark. Retired middle  
school teacher. Sunday school teacher. Widow, artist, gardener. 
Adorned the altar at All Saints Episcopal Church with 
hand-embroidered linens. 
</P>
<P>
	--James Harrison, 21, Paragould, Ark. Church music major at  
Ouachita Baptist University in Arkadelphia. A bass-baritone in 
school choir, returning from choir tour of Germany. 
</P>
<P>
	--Betty Ingram, 69, Russellville, Ark. Retired college secretary.  
Doted on nieces and nephews. Enjoyed tours with group that included 
other Russellville victims. 
</P>
<P>
	--Gordon McLerran, 64, Russellville, Ark. Retired chemist,  
amateur astronomer, spoke German and Spanish, avid fisherman. Was 
returning from visit to Britain, where he was researching his 
Scottish roots. 
</P>
<P>
	--Joyce McLerran, 65, Russellville, Ark. Made Southwestern-style  
pottery, played cards and cooked Tex-Mex food. Worked for an 
insurance company. She and husband Gordon had been high school 
sweethearts. 
</P>
<P>
	--Debra Ann Sattari, 38, Concord, Calif. Food and beverage  
manager at country club in Vallejo, Calif. Petrified of flying, but 
was traveling to Little Rock to meet friend she met on Internet. 
Mother of one. 
</P>
<P>
	--Judy Thacker, 53, Russellville, Ark. Vice president of River  
Valley Bank. An avid jogger, helped plan the Pope County Heart Walk 
scheduled for next week. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
