<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Golf, Family Keep Jordan Happy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) -- Michael Jordan avoids attending and  
watching basketball games so he can separate himself from the sport 
and help his fans do the same. 
</P>
<P>
	``As much as I can stay away from it, the easier the ties are  
broken,'' he said Friday. ``I don't want to be in a situation that 
I can't deal with being away from it, so I stay away from it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	That's why Jordan didn't follow through on a promise to visit  
the United Center this season. 
</P>
<P>
	``The fans need to understand that this is my final decision,''  
he said. ``Basketball is over for me in terms of playing in front 
of crowds and representing the city of Chicago and playing on 
teams. 
</P>
<P>
	``I must get away from it so that people can leave that part of  
my life in the past.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Jordan quit the Chicago Bulls in January, saying he was 99.9  
percent sure he would never again play in the NBA. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm approaching 100 percent,'' he said. ``The longer I stay  
away from the game and get more involved in my kids' activity, that 
99.9 starts to formulate more in the direction of 100.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Asked if he has any thoughts about playing next season, Jordan  
replied, ``None at all.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``I deep down realize it was the best move that I made,'' he  
said. ``I'm very happy with my decision. I'm very happy with the 
way my life is headed.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Jordan's life in retirement includes spending time with his  
wife, Juanita, and their three children, traveling, playing golf 
and developing business ventures. 
</P>
<P>
	He says he helps his kids with their homework, puts them to bed,  
and eats breakfast and dinner with his family, activities he never 
had time for during his playing days. 
</P>
<P>
	And, yes, he really does drive the carpool.  
</P>
<P>
	``The fun thing about it -- this is kind of scary to even mention  
-- but my little girl loves for me to take her to school on my 
motorcycle. It was something I could never do before,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	His daily workouts are history, and the only time he picks up a  
basketball is to play with his kids. 
</P>
<P>
	``The only exercise I've had over the last month or two months  
is walking in Ireland and Scotland on the golf course,'' he said. 
``That was a lot of work.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Jordan said his attempt two months ago to buy a half-interest in  
the Charlotte Hornets is dead. 
</P>
<P>
	``Will that ever change? Maybe, but I'm not going to search it  
out,'' he said. ``I'm happy with the things I'm involved in.'' 
</P>
<P>
	That includes the November launch of his new fragrance, Jordan  
by Michael. He has teamed again with designer Bijan for a new scent 
three years after his namesake cologne became a hit. Jordan was in 
Beverly Hills to shoot the advertising campaign, which will feature 
his wife for the first time. 
</P>
<P>
	Jordan wants to reduce his endorsements, including those in  
which he is merely a spokesman, in favor of ventures that allow him 
to be creative and take a hands-on approach. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm trying to cut back because the most valuable thing to me  
now is time,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Six months into retirement, Jordan said he's a happier person.  
</P>
<P>
	``I smile a lot more than I used to,'' he said. ``Now all I have  
to pay attention to is my family and my kids.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990605.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-05 12:30:07 </DATE_TIME>
