<HEADLINE> Burn 5, MetroStars 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Jason Kreis had two goals and two  
assists Saturday night to lead the Dallas Burn to a 5-2 victory 
over the New York-New Jersey MetroStars. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the third in four games for Dallas, while the  
MetroStars, playing without a foreign player in their lineup, lost 
their third straight. It was the worst loss of the season for New 
York-New Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
	John Jairo Trellez flicked a glancing header into the upper  
right corner after a cross from Mark Santel in the 31st minute to 
give the Burn a 1-0 lead. Santel played the ball in from just 
outside the box after taking a short corner from Kreis. 
</P>
<P>
	Santel made it 2-0 eight minutes later when he ran onto a pretty  
lead pass from Kreis, turned rookie defender Kevin Knight around 
and carried the ball into the box. From there he rolled a low shot 
into the right corner of the goal. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars got one back in the 52nd minute when Mike  
Sorber's shot from the top of the box took a crazy bounce off the 
right post and skidded across the goal to the foot of Brian Kelly 
who knocked it home. 
</P>
<P>
	The goal ended a 335-minute scoring drought for the MetroStars  
against the Burn. 
</P>
<P>
	Seven minutes later the Burn made it 3-1 after Kreis fought off  
Sorber and Mike Duhaney in the New York-New Jersey box following a 
long punt by Dallas goalkeeper Matt Jordan. Once he controlled the 
ball, Kreis turned quickly and slipped it into the net. 
</P>
<P>
	Kreis added his second goal of the match and 10th of the season  
in the 66th minute when he took a pass from Dante Washington, 
pulled MetroStars' keeper Mike Ammann off his line and drilled in a 
low left-footed shot. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas' Brian Haynes scored in the 77th minute and the  
MetroStars closed the scoring in the 84th minute when Billy Walsh 
headed in Peter Villegas' corner kick. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
