<HEADLINE> Missing Students' Bodies Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BAVINGTON, Pa. (AP) -- Prosecutors say they plan to seek murder  
charges against two of three suspects already jailed for the 
disappearance of two college students, now that the victims' bodies 
have been found. 
</P>
<P>
	The bodies of Aaron Land, 20, and Brian Muha, 18, were  
discovered in the woods Friday after a three-day search through 
swamps and waist-high grass along a highway. 
</P>
<P>
	The victims were students at Franciscan University in  
Steubenville, Ohio, 15 miles west of here and a short distance from 
the Pennsylvania-West Virginia line. Police believe they were 
kidnapped Monday from their apartment during a burglary, robbed and 
shot to death. 
</P>
<P>
	Prior to the discovery of the bodies, Ohio authorities charged  
Terrell Rhaim Yarbrough, 18, of Pittsburgh and Nathan D. Herring, 
18, of Steubenville, Ohio, with kidnapping, burglary and robbery. 
Both were being held on more than $2 million bond. 
</P>
<P>
	A third suspect, 16-year-old Brandon Young of Steubenville,  
Ohio, was charged in juvenile court with receiving stolen property. 
He was held without bond. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said two of the three are suspected in the students'  
deaths. 
</P>
<P>
	A grand jury will now be asked to consider murder charges, said  
Stephen Stern, an Ohio prosecutor. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
