<HEADLINE> Fighting Falcon Wins Cinema Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Fighting Falcon took the lead  
approaching the far turn and went on to win Saturday's $110,000 
Cinema Handicap at Hollywood Park by one length over Eagleton. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Brice Blanc and carrying 119 pounds, Fighting Falcon  
covered 1 1/8 miles on turf in 1:48 and paid $7.40, $3.40 and $2.80. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the fourth in eight lifetime starts for Fighting  
Falcon and was worth $66,000, raising the career earnings of the 
3-year-old son of Manila to $183,805. 
</P>
<P>
	Eagleton crossed the finish line a half-length in front of Major  
Hero and returned $3.60 and $3. 
</P>
<P>
	Major Hero, a 15-1 long shot, was a half-length ahead of  
Bristolville at the wire and paid $5.60 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Crowning Storm, the 3-2 favorite in the 53rd running of the race  
for 3-year-olds, finished fifth, followed by Mr. Reignmaker, 
Queensland Star and Man Of The Sea. In Frank's Honor was scratched. 
  	   	
