<HEADLINE> United 1, Crew 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Diego Sonora executed a perfect give-and-go  
with Roy Lassiter and scored his first goal of the season in the 
65th minute Saturday night, giving D.C. United a 1-0 victory over 
the Columbus Crew in a match between the Eastern Conference's top 
teams. 
</P>
<P>
	The win extended United's unbeaten streak to five as it last  
lost May 1 at Chicago. Columbus remained winless in 10 trips to 
Washington. 
</P>
<P>
	United had numerous scoring chances but couldn't convert until  
Sonora and Lassiter connected. Sonora started the play by sending a 
ball to Lassiter in the middle of the box. 
</P>
<P>
	Teammate Richie Williams jumped over the rolling ball, which  
momentarily froze the Columbus defense. Lassiter then touched it 
out to the on-rushing Sonora, who fired it past Columbus goalie 
Mark Dougherty 
</P>
<P>
	Lassiter's six-game goal-scoring streak was stopped, but the  
forward had a number of chances. He nearly scored a few minutes 
after Sonora's goal, but Columbus defender Mike Lapper jumped into 
the goal as Dougherty was down and knocked Lassiter's shot away. 
</P>
<P>
	United often kept the ball in the Columbus end, forcing  
Dougherty to make 12 saves. Goalie Tom Presthus was rarely tested 
for D.C., finishing with just four saves. 
</P>
<P>
	All four of Columbus' losses have been shutouts.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
