<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Slayings Could Be By Serial Killer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Police believe a serial killer may be  
responsible for strangling three women whose bodies have been found 
in a city park within the last several weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	The latest victim, identified as 17-year-old Alexandria Nicole  
Ison, was found Wednesday in Portland's Forest Park, popular with 
hikers and joggers. 
</P>
<P>
	Her body was discovered about a quarter-mile from where the  
other victims were found. That, along with the women's similar 
drug-related pasts, led police to believe the killings were the 
work of the same person. 
</P>
<P>
	Autopsies showed 28-year-old Lilla Faye Moler, discovered May 7,  
had been in the park for up to two months. Police say Stephanie 
Lynn Russell, 26, discovered while police searched for Moler, was 
likely killed within a week of being found. 
</P>
<P>
	Workers at a downtown clinic for homeless youths said they last  
saw Ison on May 18. 
</P>
<P>
	Police Chief Charles Moose said there will be a special task  
force of 12 detectives assigned to the cases. He said investigators 
have no suspects. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
