<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Casino Ship Evacuated After Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RIVIERA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- A fire in the engine room of a casino  
ship forced the evacution of 143 passengers and crew. 
</P>
<P>
	No passengers were injured, but one crewman was treated at the  
scene of Friday's fire. Authorities were unsure what started the 
fire. 
</P>
<P>
	The 156-foot SunCruz Casino ship had not yet left the dock while  
officials waited for a large party. The fire broke out just after 7 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're very fortunate it was in the docks and we were able to  
evacuate everyone immediately,'' said Fire-Rescue Chief Darrel 
Donatto. ``The crew handled it very well.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A crew member told The Palm Beach Post that he shut down the  
generator because smoke was coming out of it, which apparently 
extinguished the fire. Donatto said the fire was out when 
firefighters arrived. 
</P>
<P>
	SunCruz refunded the $10 fee to passengers, gave them a free  
cruise for another day and the promise of a free drink. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
