<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Padres Recall Pitcher Will Cunnane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- The San Diego Padres recalled right-hander Will  
Cunnane from Triple-A Las Vegas on Saturday and announced they will 
request unconditional release waivers on left-hander Ed Vosberg, 
who refused an outright assignment to Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
	Cunnane dominated the Pacific Coast League, going 2-1 with eight  
saves and a 0.55 ERA in 24 appearances. He was with the Padres for 
all of 1997 and part of 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Vosberg had no record and a 9.72 ERA in 15 relief appearances.  
He missed all of 1998 after undergoing shoulder surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	San Diego also signed second baseman Carlos Baerga and  
outfielder Wayne Kirby to minor league contracts and assigned them 
to Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
	Baerga, who had been playing for Cincinnati's Triple-A club, was  
released by the Reds on Friday so he could sign with San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
	Baerga's contract calls for him to be promoted to the majors by  
a certain date or he can again seek free agency. 
</P>
<P>
	San Diego general manager Kevin Towers said signing Baerga is an  
insurance policy for the Padres, who have been ravaged by injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	Baerga made his big league debut with the Padres in 1986. He and  
Kirby played with the New York Mets last year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
