<HEADLINE> Banshee Breeze Wins at Churchill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Banshee Breeze battled with Silent Eskimo  
down the stretch to win by a head in the $309,333 Fleur De Lis for 
fillies and mares at Churchill Downs on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Banshee Breeze, who captured the Eclipse Award as champion  
3-year-old filly last year, covered 1 1/8 miles in 1:50 and paid $2.60 
and $2.10 as the 1-5 favorite. 
</P>
<P>
	Silent Eskimo set a slow pace and gave way grudgingly in the  
stretch and paid $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Meadow Vista finished another 4 1/2 lengths back in third. With the  
field reduced to four after Whoozie was a late scratch, there was 
no show wagering. 
</P>
<P>
	Owned by James Tafel and the Jayeff B Stables and trained by  
Carl Nafzger, the 4-year-old daughter of Unbridled earned $197,718 
to boost her career bankroll to $2,043,968. It Banshee Breeze's 
first victory at Churchill Downs in four starts. 
</P>
