<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Art's Conquest Wins NJ Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Art's Conquest took the lead deep  
in the stretch and gave driver Mike Lachance and trainer Brett 
Pelling their second straight win in the $500,000 SBOA-New Jersey 
Classic on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Art's Conquest, who posted the fastest winning time last week in  
the three eliminations for this race for 3-year-old pacers, 
bettered his own stakes record by covering the mile in 1:50. 
</P>
<P>
	Royalflush Hanover, driven by Luc Ouellette, finished a length  
back in second place. It was only a nose back to Grinfromeartoear, 
the John Campbell-driven colt who was the other part of Pelling's 
favored entry. 
</P>
<P>
	Pelling also finished 1-3 in last year's New Jersey Classic with  
Shady Character winning and Al For President finishing third. 
</P>
<P>
	Art's Conquest paid $3.60, $2.40 and $2.60 in winning his third  
straight race and earning $250,000 for Brittany Farms of 
Versailles, Ky. and Daisy Acres of Astoria, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's an honest little horse, never does anything wrong,'' said  
Pelling, whose has seen the son of Artsplace improve since losing a 
little extra weight the past month. ``He deserves this.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Royalflush Hanover paid $3 and $2.80 in losing for the first  
time in six starts this year. Grinfromeartoear, the winner of last 
year's Woodrow Wilson Pace, was $2.60 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Art's Conquest got a perfect trip behind Royalflush Hanover.  
</P>
<P>
	``Speed has been holding up pretty good, but I was right behind  
Luc until the top of the stretch and those two in front had to work 
real hard,'' Lachance said. 
</P>
<P>
	Campbell got Grinfromeartoear to the front early from the No. 8  
post and they led the 10-horse field through the first quarter in 
27 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	Cam's Rocket, with Kevin Sizer in the bike, took the lead on the  
backstretch, but Campbell quickly took it back and had the lead at 
the half-mile mark in 54 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	As the field reached the top of the stretch, Grinfromeartoear  
had a three-quarter length lead over Royalflush Hanover with Art's 
Conquest another 1 3/4 lengths back and closing. 
</P>
<P>
	In the stretch, those three horses -- the three elimination  
winners last weekend -- were the only ones with a shot at winning. 
</P>
<P>
	Lachance had Art's Conquest pacing the fastest on the outside in  
the final 100 yards and he put the others away. Royalflush Hanover, 
who was in the middle of the pack, just got his nose in front of 
Grinfromeartoear at the wire. 
</P>
<P>
	``He got to the front easy enough,'' Campbell said. ``I was able  
to control the pace but he just didn't have enough power to 
finish.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Shark St Partners finished fourth and was followed by Old  
Buzzard, Falcon's Icon, Relentless Yankee, Art De Triomphe, Card 
Shuttle and Cam's Rocket. 
</P>
<P>
	In the $250,000 Miss New Jersey final for 3-year-old fillies,  
Jack Moiseyev and Woodsie and Buster held off Celebrity Ball to win 
by a half-length in 1:52.1. The Brian Magie-trained filly paid 
$11.80, $4.40 and $4 in winning for the second time in five starts. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
